Hubs to @momwithtriplets

social_posts.post_text:
Hello. I write to you today from the trenches as we prepare for battle. We have delegated evenings of planning for this moment. The required supplies have landed. The personnel is prepped. And we stand before you today. Ready. 
.
The toilets placed. Diapers are put away. Interest in the potty is here. This weekend. We start to LEARN THE POTTY!!!! 
.
For this reason, we will go dark for the majority of the weekend. We will come back with tales to tell, that I have no doubt. Wish us luck! 
.
#pottytraining #pottylearning #inthetrenches

When @momwithtriplets and I got Millie Dog, we had read around 5-10 books on puppy training. We had all the useful resources & gadgets. We were ready. And then we got Millie. And nothing we read worked with her. She would spit treats out. She didn’t care for cuddles. We were panicking that we were in over our heads and we were going to have to be those people who say “she never does this!” as she steals a random toddlers sandwich at the park…even though we all know she always does this. Low and behold, we eventually figured out Millie Dogs motivations and she is the best dog we have ever had.
.
An analogous story appears to be unfolding with potty training (note, there will be lots of potty talk going forward 😉). Day 1 went about as well as expected. Accidents all over the place. Positive encouragement. A small win of a 1/4 pee for Logan. No worries…big change. They’ll do better tomorrow. 
.
Tomorrow came and day 2 we had less accidents but the same amount of pee made it in the potty. Which was essentially 4 drops from Logan. Some doubt creeping in…
.
Day 3 was all types of mind games. Only Logan seemed to understand where pee should go but only if we prompted her to try at the right place and right time. Rowen and Addie - no care in the world. Standing in their own urine? Not like they enjoyed it but essentially “butler, clean this up so that I may be on my way.” Felt really defeated and wasn’t taking this parenting L well.
.
At day 3 nap time, I was 100% ok with calling it quits and coming back in a couple weeks/months. This is stressing us out. It’s not a big deal. Every kid nails it eventually. But we are 2.5 days in and it wasn’t a guarantee the next time would be any easier so we decided to carry on and talk about it that night. 
.
Well all be darn. They woke up from nap ready to pee in that dang potty. We had some accidents still but everybody peed in the potty successfully. Rowen and Logan turned a corner. Addie got a small win. It was rejuvenating.
.
I’m out of space on this caption, so this post will be left as a cliffhanger (I’m sure you’re on the edge of your seat 😜) and I’ll update in a couple days. But day 5 is going well so far…

Ok. That’s the only word my brain has to offer after day 10 of potty training.
.
Seriously a little mushy in there right now. I feel like potty training is your hazing ritual into toddlerhood.
.
I’m not going to pick up daily from where I left off, but I will say, without having complete success yet, I do wish one of the 7494638 opinions we got on how to best potty train was…prepare AND be OK with pivoting.
.
This may sound like I’m whining because I do feel like I’ve taken my first major parenting L, but you watch the videos, read the books and are feeling confident but then the reality hits that you have 3 babies and everyone dishing out this info has 1.
.
One would have a mess and while we clean that, another is peeing on the magna-tiles. One would have a success, and while we walk them to dump it, another is pooping on their learning tower. We simply couldn’t keep up, making it harder for them to learn that connection between feeling the need to potty and getting their butt on the potty. But they sure felt the growing stress of mom and (particularly) dad having to clean up a lot of s h i t and constantly prompting someone to go to the potty.
.
Logan has always been eager to learn. She got it the quickest. Once Rowen got her first win, she went neck and neck with Logan. Addie though (bless her heart), she was/is more hesitant. And we all seemed to stagnate after day 4 or 5.
.
And here is where we would have done things differently. We started with the old fashion naked route. However, at day 4-5 when we initially felt some of the pushback, we wish we put them back into pull-ups instead of pushing through and hoping for another breakthrough like day 3. This is what we did yesterday and taking our foot off the gas has been a big lift. Selfishly, I needed it, but the girls also seem much happier and relaxed. Best part is…they still ask to go potty. What a wasted few days of extra stress!
.
I know grandmas out there! “You’re putting too much pressure on yourselves, everyone learns eventually!” Potty training is weird though in the moment. It’s a combo of mistakes and successes, that it’s hard to know which direction to go. Let’s see how things keep on keeping on…

If you make it too obvious that you are taking a picture, it will disturb the taters and it will cause them to tantrum. That’s why mom is creeping in slowly from the side as dad and grandma pulled the ol’ bait and switch of pretending that we were seeing if they were as tall as a baby giraffe when really, *enter evil laugh*, we were getting a picture! Logan was definitely on to us though. She’s a quick one that tot.
.
Had a grand old time at the zoo over the weekend waddling around to see the animals. They loved it. Only issue (if it can be called that) we are currently facing is nobody wants to go in the wagon. They either want to walk or be held or go on shoulders. It’s just a bit tiring - plus these potatoes are getting plump! Makes for a good show though when you just can’t do it any longer and you’re leaving the zoo with three babies screaming to be held from the wagon. Everyone coming into the zoo got a free show though from this circus leaving.
.
ARL
.
#zoo #tripletsofinstagram

I have read that you cannot give your children too many hugs. However, there’s gotta be a point where they’re getting a little too greedy with their hug and up demands.
.
Toddlerhood is an exciting mix of new learnings, playful joy, good times…and challenges. However, the girls are in a verrrrry challenging “needy” stage. Which sounds cute if you’re an outsider looking in. But take my word for it - it gets old fast and I don’t even take the brunt of it. @momwithtriplets is the go-to for comfort, bless her heart, and I’ve still had enough. Touched out would be an understatement. 
.
I think I’m starting to understand all the “oh just wait until the terrible twos” comments. It’s easy to get swept up in the difficult stages of toddlerhood because it is difficult. Your existence is quite literally tied to their demands which are constant and completely irrational. It can make you feel trapped.
.
But then they all want to cuddle together in a crib, give hugs while infectiously laughing and all of a sudden there’s nowhere else you would ever want to be.
.
Doesn’t make the difficult moments go away, but it does make it all worth it.
.
RLA
.
#cuddlepuddle #tripletsofinstagram #terribletwos

Wooo! Been a wild ride that I hope is coming to a stop here soon and I don’t want to get on it again.
.
Few weeks back, we started feeling a little down. Sore throats, runny dose and what not. It made for a fussy week. They are never fun, but it happens.
.
Then, after a little party with friends and their kids (and friends if you’re reading this, I’m not blaming you! We had an amazing time! It’s just a part of the story arc :)), we all started feeling down again a couple days after. Turns out, some of the kiddos had hand, foot and mouth disease and weren’t showing symptoms yet. And yes, that’s the actual name of it and I too needed to google what the heck it is when we were told about it. But essentially we all caught the nasties. And it’s been nasty for us. And hit everyone at different times, but at similar, surprisingly uncomfortable rates.
.
Add to that molars coming in. They’re gnawing on their hands like dogs on a bone.
.
And, there is a cherry on top but for the sake of them taking care of me when I’m back in diapers, I’ll keep it on the DL. Or until I find a way to describe it gracefully at a later date.
.
I don’t think I’m exaggerating when I say at least 80-90% of all wake windows for the last two weeks have been managing a crying baby needing to be held or whatever.
.
Anywho. That’s a little taste of why it’s been all quiet on the triplet front. One of our biggest battles to date. But I think we will come out on top God-willing.
.
LRA across the couch.
.
#beingsickstinks #livetoseeanotherday

I asked @momwithtriplets if she had any photos I could use for a post. She didn’t. I tried to take some pictures but there was no way of getting full cooperation and everyone in the picture. So we threw up this little tripod with a Bluetooth button and the girls enjoyed it…for the most part - they liked seeing themselves on the screen I think haha. Millie couldn’t be bothered to get outta the way but, that’s how it goes. I seriously have no idea how those perfect little “influencer” pages get such quality photos. It actually impresses me in a weird way. The amount of time and patience it would take for that to happen under this roof would be staggering.
.
Everyone is feeling better now and slowly but surely returning to their old selves which is a welcomed change of pace. Now  if the weather could warm up so we can open the back door and run about I’d appreciate it.
.
LRA
.
#happyfriday #familytime

Need some advice on how to travel with your triplets? You are in the right place! I present to you a few travel tips for how you too, can travel with your 2.5 year old triplets. 
.
Tip 1 - Wear your “Yes, my hands are full” sweater. Granted, this will be covered by backpacks and/or babies the entire time so nobody will see it, but you can try to direct the 27th person of the day who says that incredibly unique phrase to the back of your sweater when available.
.
Tip 2 - this one is for the fellas. Guys, it helps a lot to have a wife who thinks about the things you do not - like packing an entire activity bag. The colored pencils and paper you would stuff in your backpack is NOT sufficient for extended periods of entertainment. Thank goodness for @momwithtriplets.
.
Tip 3 - the triplet stroller (should you bring one) will most likely be used strictly as a bag carrier so…1) you don’t worry that much about how you will possibly carry everything in the airport but 2) consider the size of your car and luggage because you may encounter issues there.
.
Tip 4 - Whether we deserve it or not, people tend to provide more grace to us triplet parents. Flight attendants will ignore that child in your lap with the seat belt sign on. You only have to do the metal detector and not that full on body scanner thing at security. People will praise you for juggling the insanity despite cries on the plane. The attention can be annoying but it does have its perks.
.
Tip 5 - renting a car and car seats? Look up how to install before arriving otherwise you will have to figure that crap out on the fly and it’s a huge pain in the butt.
.
Tip 6 - I could probably do a ton more but my final tip. On the way there, remind yourselves that you expect it to be equal parts fun, crazy, annoying, exciting, irritating, etc. That gives you an hour or so before you forget when you just got the final bag on the conveyor belt at security, pick up a crying baby while pushing a stroller around people and the TSA agent tells you you need to take your shoes off.
.
Good luck to everyone on your travels! Will update more later ;) 
.
RLA
.
#triplettravels #firstplaneride

@momwithtriplets and I met in college working at a summer sports camp (we joke as being one of the last couples to get together in the pre-online dating world). Some of our best friends come from camp and this trip allowed us to celebrate the marriage of one of them AND also get to bring our kids together with another - who to his credit knew @momwithtriplets and I would get married before we did. It was a really special moment (friends, we love you very much). 
.
Even though we brought our weather with us, the ladies were also much more accepting of the beach in warmer climates. Don’t mind Bean - someone just said the phrase that shall not be said “take a picture” and she wasn’t down for that.
.
ALR
.
#friendsforever #beachtrip

These photos are almost two years apart to the day. They are even in the same order and it was just a happy accident. Definitely one of my new favorites. 
.
I saw this clip from the Office that goes “I wish there was a way to know you were in the good old days before you actually left them.”
.
I try to think I’m always in the good old days (not always successful) but looking back at memories like this is always a little reminder that the old cliche of how quickly time will pass certainly has some truth in it.
.
Now that I’ve reminisced on that glorious beard (hehehe joking!)…it really is crazy to see how much they’ve grown and changed in two short years. And if that second picture doesn’t make clear why we called them potatoes, I don’t know what will!
.
LRA
.
#babypotatoes #tatertots #stillgotit

Scooter queens update. Thanks to the great PNW winters, we've only been able to dream about hopping back on the @microkickboard. Luckily, the sun broke through the clouds this weekend and our excitement can't be understated. FYI - no better time to grab a @microkickboard of your own. They are running a 20% off spring sale today through April 2 (link in bio).
.
Also. Learning is weird. Considering our last time using them, we were at roughly 80% pushing them around backwards and 20% kinda sorta scootering, this was not a progression I was anticipating. Logan Bean jumped right on and started pushing her way across the entire street. I think that confidence encouraged Addie Goose and Rowen Rooster because they followed behind quickly.
.
Granted, there is still a lingering fondness of pushing them around backwards but we are now at probably 60% scootering and 40% backwards pushing. Progress!
.
And again, best quality scooters around, tons of colors and options for all ages, and a favorite outdoor activity for us. Sale on now! Link in bio!
.
LAR
.
#scooter #cantwaitforsummer #ad

Sayyyy cheeeeeseee.
.
I didn’t have much for this post. I just liked this picture. But then I was reading some article headline about the importance of the first 3 years of development. Which then I could only think about how I got sassy with Logan this morning because she threw a fit about getting the dog bowl when I asked but really wanted to fill it up but Addie was super down so when Addie got the bowl Logan was sad that Addie was now filling it up and I clapped back at her like “I asked you to help and you said no so now I don’t want your help.” Which was true. She was being a punk but I’m supposed to be the adult in the room. So then I started spiraling about how I ruined my child for being an immature knob.
.
Anyways, she was running around with Norbie’s floppy fish in her mouth and asking me to read to her like 3 minutes later. And then I actually read the article and it essentially said to go wrong you have to go reallllly wrong. So I felt better.
.
Moral to this ramble is to read the whole article. And I’m sorry about that Bean. I still stand by you being super annoying about it though.
.
This is your brain on triplets.
.
No initials because…well…let’s just see who needs help still.
.
#thisisyourbrainontriplets

Mom asked for this as a reel and I agree. Plus bonus Norbie appearance.
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #parents #parenting #dadlife #girldad

Let’s go have a good rest of our week!
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #parents #parenting #dadlife #girldad

“Say cheese” has been effective at getting smiles for pictures. They haven’t quite connected smiling at the camera, but you take what you get sometimes. 
.
It’s been asked enough times that I do think a potty training update is in order. I don’t really love talking about this stuff because potty training has this religiosity about it that is overwhelming. With that said, what we are doing is perfect and anyone saying/doing otherwise is a lunatic psychopath (I’m kidding, of course!). 
.
We started with a plan but the results didn’t follow. Whether we started too early, or didn’t prepare them or enough or whatever is besides the point at this stage. We had some early wins and positive steps but essentially the stress won. They have a little all for one, one for all mentality and if someone isn’t down they all may not be down. This works in the opposite way as well but in this instance, it did not. 
.
We have switched over to a more child-led approach and interest currently comes and goes but we are in pull-up’s, encouraging the potty but not pressuring anymore. Maybe another proper go will be taken in the summer but for now, I can confidently say we are all much happier in pull-ups.
.
Anywayssss, that’s how the cookie crumbles sometimes. Onward we go!
.
ARL (moms lap, back, front)
.
#pottytraining #pottylearning #youliveandyoulearn

Every nap time and bedtime, they now put their bunnies into their blankies and cradle them down the hall going “shhhh”. It’s very cute, won’t lie.
.
We’ve been having a great couple weeks around here. *knock on wood* for some reason it does feel like the calm before the storm but it’s probably because I’m still recovering from potty training traumas.
.
But just been a blast. Yeah, sister disputes and a little pouty here and there, but in general, good vibes these days. Also feels like the vocabulary is exploding and I’m going to blink and they’ll be asking me why every 4 seconds. Can’t wait actually. Keep it up ladies! 
.
LRA
.
#goodvibes #tripletsofinstagram

You know when people say something like “you’re gonna blink and next thing you know they’re talking full blown sentences”? I do believe I’m in the process of blinking right now. It seems like the gains are becoming exponential which is fun.
.
At the same time, I’m genuinely curious if they’ll develop their own little internal language along with it. They’ll be times when I’ll ask them to feed Millie and 3 babies will look at each other, murmur some nonsense and then scatter in different directions with obvious clarity in terms of what their delegated responsibility is. That’s just one example of many. Mom and I will often look at each other and go “what the heck just happened?” 
.
And lastly, the picture is a new game where they essentially take turns laying on the floor to get smothered by their sisters. I’m all for it. May their love for each other carry on forever.
.
ARL
.
#triplethelove #languagelearning

Rowen playing a little game a peekaboo with the camera here. 
.
We are still running the Earth Day giveaway with @subpod and would love y’all to put your name in the hat…or should I say bin. Because their compost bins are phenomenal and are the best way to reduce waste and make amazing compost. As a wannabe gardener who built a bunch of garden beds, I can confidently say it is a really amazing product and is Tater approved!
.
If you want to enter, like the post, tag 2 friends and enter through the link in my bio! US, UK and AUS. You can still like the post for cute Taters.
.
Man, are we excited for the ☀️ 
.
LAR
.
#compost #garden #growyourown

We are a few months out from what I’ve been told are known as the “terrorist threes”. There is something strange about parenting where every stage has some negative connotation attached to it and is also the biggest blessing that you’ll miss when it’s gone.
.
I’m not buying into it other than the I’ll miss it when it’s gone. They are so much fun right now. Nothing “terrible” about the twos for us. All the tougher times were our own doings. Don’t potty train! It’s not worth it! (I’m kidding, every child is different and are ready at their own pace - I think. I don’t know. Also we could have just sucked at it). But they just have so much love and excitement about life. They just want to learn and help and play with you. Part of the reason my posting has dwindled slightly as well and I’m ok with it. It’s beautiful to be a part of.
.
Yeah, yeah. It isn’t always easy. It can be really annoying and tough when they get worked up over something that seems silly but a hug and a chat usually goes a long way. 
.
I’ll miss it when it’s gone. But I’m also pumped up for the next stages. Language is starting to hit its stride and it’s going to be really interesting and fun around here. I laugh at the thought of the crazy things they’ll say which hopefully isn’t them swearing at the Edna’s like their momma ;)
.
RLA
.
#triplets #sunsout #lunchtime

If I went to an aquarium on my own, I would probably be like “oh cool, haven’t seen a shark in a while. Anyways. Let’s go”. But something about going with kids and seeing their joy at some fishies and other animals kind of resets you back to your previous settings of amazement.
.
They had so much fun. Still aren’t so sure about wind as an element in general which I totally get but they certainly enjoy the sunshine and romping about some special spots with beautiful views.
.
Also, the first production run of our waterproof sock shoes have finally arrived! I would really appreciate if you could follow @meriweather_co (I changed the brand name and will name the shoe the Tater we think ;))and if you have a little one, consider grabbing by a pair! They are fantastic in rain or shine and I am really happy with the results. I’ll do some more videos showing how well they work. Huge thank you to everyone who supported early. It means the world. It’s been fun making our very own product from our experiences with the girls. Have a look 👀 
.
LAR
.
#aquarium #beachweekend

Little demo video for the waterproof sock-shoe I made for the girls and are now available for sale. The brand on IG is @meriweather_co and would love a follow if you could. And would be humbled if you purchased a pair for your little ones! Thanks everybody!
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #smallbusiness #wishmeluck

Spring has sprung over here as we welcome it in with our annual tradition of romping around the tulip farms.
.
Another thing has sprung and I produced my first round of waterproof sock shoes (it actually happened!). This project has a lot of effort and love behind it. The idea came straight from our experiences with the girls and I’m really proud of the product. I would really appreciate if you could follow the brand at @meriweather_co and if you have little ones, please consider ordering a pair. I know it’s not the best of timing for a waterproof sock shoe with summer approaching but they are great for rain or shine as well, and you’ll always be prepared for a possible wet occasion :) 
.
And thank you to everyone who has already or are considering supporting. Sometimes I sit and laugh that I was essentially a social media recluse prior to the girls arrival to now having over 100k people following and supporting our journey with triplets. It’s been fun, won’t lie, and I love looking back on the memories.
.
I also promise this channel won’t become a sponsored channel just pushing the shoes all the time. I’ll tag them a bunch :) but I will keep this just “day-in-the-life” as I always have. You’ll just get bonus content over at @meriweather_co :) Much love!
.
LAR
.
#tulips #smallbusiness #triplets

We went “camping” in our backyard this weekend which is one of those things that can go one of two ways. A grand old time where everyone enjoys themselves or an epic disaster. It was the former and I’m amped up about that because I love camping and we have a trip planned this summer and we wanted the girls to be prepared for it.
.
Bedtimes don’t exist when you are sleeping outside but you make some compromises. They loved sitting around the fire for about 2 minutes but were more into their new lanterns a follower sent us (thank you!).
.
By about 10pm with everyone still wide awake we did some stargazing.
.
In the end, we are happy campers as they say 🏕️ 
.
RLA
.
#happycamper #backyardcamping #triplets

I wanted the way she said “bald baby” on my timeline forever.
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #parenting #parents #dadlife #girldad

Dear Addie, Logan and Rowen. Let’s slow it down a bit, ok? This whole growing up thing is overrated anyways and y’all are getting tall and the whole rapidly increasing vocabulary thing is throwing me for a loop. It’s all just moving a little too fast for me at the minute.
.
Don’t get me wrong, I appreciate that your favorite activities are mowing the lawn like dad and taking care of baby like mom. It’s very sweet. And I love seeing you learn and grow. It’s my favorite thing in the world. But I think I’d be good with hitting the pause button for a bit.
.
Anyways, lemme know if you get this message. Talk soon, dad. 
.
RLA
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #theygrowupsofast

Logan Bean with some serious self-control to not push her sister haha just found this interaction amusing.
.
#parentingproblems #triplets #tripletsofinstagram #dadlife

Here’s our parenting hack so you too can get these ridiculous cheese faces for photos. I’m not saying we made it up but it was a happy accident. We learned that if you show them the pictures after you take them, it reconditions them a bit to not think their entire world is caving in when you simply use the word “photo” in a sentence. It’s not 100% but it increases the odds substantially.
.
This photo here is also to showcase some of these @lovevery goodies since we’ve got some questions on them. We find our girls always gravitate towards their stuff and we love them. They have little boxes that are sold by the age of your child. The little camper van and wooden figures and sleeping bags has been a massive hit with our recent camping voyage. There’s a link in my bio to check em out if interested.
.
You can almost see their personalities in the way they cheese so I’ll have to put one of those together again as well.
.
RAL
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #saycheese #lovevery

Does anybody know at what age they just want to lay down and cuddle? Asking for a friend. I enjoy their little busy selves but I would love to just be able to lay down and watch a flick at some point, ya know what I mean? 
.
Either way, I’ll be patient. They are in growth mode right now and the learning is off the charts. I blinked and yesterday they were counting to five. Which I didn’t know they could do. But they can. Life comes at you fast.
.
I have a theory that your perception of time changes as you get older or under certain life events. As a kid, I remember a day could feel like a month. Now as a dad, a month feels like years. I just look at pictures from a year ago and it’s like I’m looking at different humans. Feels like yesterday but also, so long ago.
.
Anyways, that’s enough philosophizing for today.
.
ALR
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #parents #parenting

I’m currently writing this after I just found a short window to exercise for the first time in I don’t know how long due to the fact I stepped on the scale after the girls did one day and noticed a new second digit I had never seen before. I am currently incapacitated but confident I will walk again.
.
Especially since one of my favorite things is going on walks with the girls. A few weeks ago Addie was having a tough time and I asked if she wanted to go on a walk with daddy and she agreed and now there are regular requests to “Walk. Daddy. Outside”. Which I admittedly love that a tiny little ask that was really just trying to get Addie to stop crying at mommy forever is now a little moment that has stuck with her…and Logan and Rowen. Since obviously Addie got a walk, they all wanted to walk. Which we did. And it helped Addie cool her jets.
.
Walks heal a lot of wounds.
.
Also, what’s your favorite color of their @meriweather_co shoes? Yellow won the poll the other day by a significant margin. 
.
ALR
.
#walkwalkwalk #triplets #tripletsofinstagram

Just a minute of best friends holding hands
.
#triplets #tripletsofinstagram #parenting #parents #dadlife #girldad

This didn’t use to be my favorite season. I’ve always been privy to winter because I love snow. But after living in a rainy place and having triplets, things done changed and I am especially joyful for this time of year. Sun is shining, garden is blooming, and bikes are out for riding.
.
I call this time of year @bunchbikes season now and as a self-proclaimed advocate for @bunchbikes I will get on my soap box…or bike seat (haha..ha) to tell you the unanticipated upgrades this little vehicle has brought to us.
.
1) increased our footprint. The girls get to go to a new park almost every afternoon now because it’s easy to hop in this guy for a few miles pedal. They especially like “shade” park as it’s called because it’s, well shaded, and the slides don’t get so hot i sweat they could melt steel.
.
2) quick trips that used to involve a car like the grocery store or library are now done in the bike oftentimes. Saves us the packing in and out and parking which is a pain in the…you know what.
.
3) when we just need a “reset” it works like a walk. An evening pedal can really help balance things out during tougher moments.
.
Anyways, I’ll end my advocacy here but I do dream of a time when bikes like this are a regular. It’s a game changer for our family.
.
Have a happy Father’s Day weekend to the dads out there.
.
LRA
.
#tripletsofinstagram #bikeride #bunchbikeseason

Woke up like this.
.
It took me a while to understand the posts I always see of parents complaining about morning and bedtime routines with their kids. Cause it feels like in the last couple of weeks the girls are wising up and have made it their mission to extend bedtime routines and the pre-morning pull-up change routines for as long as humanly possible.
.
I take a lot of pride in doing my best to give them as much space as possible to do things on their own but I’m fairly confident they have meetings in their cribs to plot and scheme on how they can extend things out. 
.

I turned 33 years of age yesterday. Here are 33 things I’ve learned since my girls turned 3.
.
I’m just kidding. I don’t have time to do that.
.
But I will share one thing about the toddler phase, as opposed to the baby phase (in my experience at least). And that’s that the baby phase requires attention 24/7 but you have a lot more downtime just chillin’ out with a baby. The toddler phase, you get the benefits of them being pretty good sleepers, but those 16 hours (aside from a good nap if you’re lucky), have absolutely zero downtime.
.
I have my struggles with this phase (meltdowns galore) but the developmental strides are a lot more fun and you become a more active participant in their play and navigation of this thing called life. But you just feel way more busy. I don’t have the same amount of time to do the little things like capturing the small moments. I have a baby to high five as she goes down the slide. Or a puzzle that must be done on my lap. Or a scratch that must be kissed.
.
There was this video or standup bit I saw once about how parents do a whole bunch of stuff and then feel like nothing was accomplished at the end of the day. It’s not true because Im confident this time spent will have its payoff but also…it resonates.
.
Either way, all is good. Love being a dad! For this picture, they begged me to pick them all up. And I STILL got it.
.

When you say “Toes must stay on the carpet during quiet time”.
.
This is one of those “yeah duh dude” thoughts. But as they have become little masters of manipulation, I kinda had an ah ha moment.
.
Our life is really routine based. We have a very similar schedule every day. Patience is my weak spot and I realized it’s almost always unhinged when the routine is a bit ruffled.
.
But then most of the fun, creative moments come when things are a bit whacky like this. But also the patience is more of a problem when they cry and whine for what are silly things to a grown adult. Such as asking me to come in their room for the 4th time to put their hair tie in…that I clearlyyyyy told them to not take out if they still wanted it in mind you. Thing is, they probably just want a little connection time with mom and dad. Anyways. Guess I was starting to think that maybe I don’t need to be so strict on a routine 100% of the time or just cause their nightlight is red and I could just be nice about putting a hair tie in after bedtime. 
.
But then again. They’re smart. And if you give ‘em an inch, they’ll take a mile and next thing you know putting that hair tie in after bedtime is part of the routine.
.
So that’s the convoluted way of saying that parenting for me has been this mind game of deciding when to let loose and when to tighten the ropes. And I haven’t sorted that out yet. I just know when I get inpatient.
.
BYE!
.
RAL
.
